                    <msContents>
                        <summary> A woodblock printed manual for the performance of the tea ceremony with sencha (infused tea) written and illustrated by Ryūkatei Ransui of Nagoya, including monochrome illustrations of the utensils required. It was originally titled Jibencharyaku but the title has been excised from the blocks and a new title substituted on the covers. The blocks for Jibencharyaku were cut in 1802, but the date at which the changes were made is unknown. Under the new title it was published by Eirakuya Tōshirō of Nagoya et al.</summary>

                        <textLang mainLang="ja" source="IANA">Japanese</textLang>

